Under the supervision the student is conducting an independent  practical project using knowledge related to applied cultural analysis.
The student:
-	is composing a research plan and aims of the study in collaboration with an external partner;
-	is conducting a practical project at an external partner;
-	presents a written work in which the collected materials, acquired experience and ethical issues are  critically analysed (e.g. methods and their application, the results etc.).
-	presents the final results of the study in a suitable media and form for the external partner.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide an opportunity for getting hands on experience in cultural analysis in collaboration with external partners (e.g. other research institution, organization, enterprise, NGO etc.).Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After successfully passing the course the student: 1.	can apply methods of applied cultural analysis while conducting a practical project at an external partner. 2.	is able to critically analyse knowledge and experience acquired during the fieldwork practice and reflects critically upon applicability (including ethical issues) of practical cultural analysis in a particular research context.
